# /auto — Thin Router

> 🐙 Autopus | {{.ProjectName}} | {{.Mode}}

ARGUMENTS: $ARGUMENTS

## Language Policy

- AI responses follow the configured project language policy. Code comments and commit messages retain their configured languages.

## Source Ownership

- Read `.autopus/project/workspace.md` first when present. It defines the root role, nested git repo boundaries, generated/runtime paths, tracking/commit policy, source-of-truth locations, and QA target routing such as `auto qa init --project-dir <repo>`.
- Resolve a SPEC as `.autopus/specs/{SPEC-ID}/spec.md`, then recursively under module roots while excluding generated and dependency directories. Stop on zero or duplicate matches.

## Subagent Delegation

- Preserve the harness subagent-first contract. `--auto` authorizes the configured pipeline; `--solo` explicitly selects a single session.
- If runtime policy prevents implicit delegation, report the constraint and request subagent opt-in or `--solo`; never silently downgrade.

## Review Convergence

- Separate finding discovery from verification. Retries verify only open findings against the new diff and keep configured retry limits.

## Generated Surface Safety

- Do not directly edit generated/runtime roots such as `.claude/**`, `.codex/**`, `.gemini/**`, `.opencode/**`, or `.autopus/plugins/**`.
- Change the canonical ADK template/source, regenerate, and exclude generated/runtime drift from commits.

## Routing Contract

1. Strip global flags while preserving their values: `--auto`, `--loop`, `--multi`, `--quality`, `--team`, `--solo`, `--model`, `--variant`, `--think`, `--ultrathink`, `--workflow`.
2. Use the first remaining token as the route. For natural-language input, perform bounded triage and select one route; without `--auto`, confirm a material route change.
3. Load exactly one detail from the table below. Do not preload other auto details or the generation-only workflow source.
4. Pass all arguments and flags unchanged to the selected detail.

